TCGA Variant calling pipelines show low agreement

This will be a quick post I want to communicate a suprising (to me, at least) result

There are, by my highly scientific estimate, about a gajillion somatic variant calling tools available. All the samples on TCGA are subject to four variant calling pipelines, whic are GDC believes are representative of the most reliable callers currently available. Each pipeline is based on a different caller you can read about all the gory pipeline details here.

But, as the title says, these four pipelines show fairly low concordance. Here for example, is a venn diagram (which I made using venn) of all the calls for the 1100 or so BRCA samples on TCGA:
